Maritime Workers Union of Nigeria (MWUN) has suspended its ongoing strike over unpaid wages to dockworkers.  The union suspended the three days strike after a meeting with the Permanent Secretary Ministry of Transportation and other stakeholders. The president general of the union, Adewale Adeyanju said yesterday that the strike was suspended following the intervention of the permanent secretary, Ministry of Transportation, Sabiu Zakari and Managing Director of the Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA), Hadiza Bala-Usman in Lagos.  Adeyanju noted that Messrs Zakari and Bala-Usman had promised to address all the grey areas affecting the staff welfare, especially the backlog allowances owed stevedoring and dockworkers. He added: “They have assured us that the issue that regards maritime staff welfare would be resolved.”